com.bluegosling.collections.concurrent

Class LockFreeLinkedBlockingDeque<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractQueue<E>
        • com.bluegosling.collections.AbstractDeque<E>
          • com.bluegosling.collections.concurrent.AbstractLockFreeBlockingDeque<E>
            • com.bluegosling.collections.concurrent.LockFreeLinkedBlockingDeque<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of element stored in the queue
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, BlockingDeque<E>, BlockingQueue<E>, Deque<E>, Queue<E>

    public class LockFreeLinkedBlockingDeque<E>
extends AbstractLockFreeBlockingDeque<E>
    A lock-free implementation of BlockingDeque, backed by a ConcurrentLinkedDeque.

    Unlike the ConcurrentLinkedDeque that backs it, this blocking deque provides an O(1) implementation of size(). An AtomicInteger is used to track the size and to also ensure that any configured capacity limit is enforced.

    This class handles blocking operations (e.g. AbstractLockFreeBlockingDeque.takeFirst(), AbstractLockFreeBlockingDeque.putLast(Object), etc.) with custom wait queues instead of using Locks and Conditions.

    Use of Iterator.remove() is discouraged. If invoked and there are multiple, equal values in the deque, the first one will be removed instead of the one last fetched by the iterator. Similarly, calling remove() on a descendingIterator() when there are multiple, equal values in the deque will result in the last one being removed, not the one last fetched by the iterator.
